&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://desktop.github.com/&#34;&gt;GitHub Desktop&lt;/a&gt; is my favorite of the free GUIs for Git. It&amp;rsquo;s made by GitHub, but there&amp;rsquo;s nothing tying it to their service. It&amp;rsquo;s just a Git client, and it will work fine with any host, or just locally. Check out GitHub&amp;rsquo;s guide: &lt;a href=&#34;https://guides.github.com/introduction/getting-your-project-on-github/&#34;&gt;Getting your project on GitHub&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
